               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170115-189-person1362">
                  ABRAHAM 
                  OAKLEY
               <interp inst="t18170115-189-person1362" type="surname" value="OAKLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170115-189-person1362" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170115-189-person1362" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol. On the 10th of January, about a quarter past ten o'clock at night, I was at the corner of Rose-lane, Spital-fields. I met the prisoner crossing the road, somebody gave an alarm, and I stopped him with the cask of blue on his shoulder; I asked him what it was, he said, it was salt, and that he got it from Mr. Saltes, in Bishopsgate-street. I asked him, where he was going to take it; he said, to the corner of Angel-alley, Whitechapel, to a cheesmonger's. I told him, it was too heavy for salt, and took him to the watch<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181701150074"></xptr>house. I went to Angel-alley, the man said, he expected no salt, nor did he know Mr. Salter; the cask was examined and found to be blue.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170115-189-person1363">
                  THOMAS 
                  HART
               <interp inst="t18170115-189-person1363" type="surname" value="HART"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170115-189-person1363" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170115-189-person1363" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I examined the cask at the watchhouse, the prisoner said it was salt; I found it to be blue.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I met a man who told me to carry it to Whitechapel, and said it was salt.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18170115-189-verdict1035" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18170115-189-verdict1035" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 21.</p>
